In a meeting in the State Dining Room, President Biden discusses the importance of oversight and accountability in government spending. He mentions the success of the Recovery Act in minimizing waste and fraud, thanks in part to the work of inspector generals like Earl Devaney. President Biden emphasizes the need for strong oversight in current and future spending, particularly in infrastructure projects, to ensure that funds are allocated based on safety and necessity rather than political considerations. He also highlights the role of inspector generals in building trust with the American people by demonstrating responsible and efficient use of taxpayer money. The President assures that inspector generals have complete independence in their investigations and encourages them to uncover both successes and failures in government programs. The meeting concludes with President Biden expressing his commitment to restoring faith in government by delivering on promises and being transparent in the use of public funds.